ğŸ“š Library Management System (Flask + MySQL + CLI)

    A full-stack Library Management System built using Flask, MySQL,
    Pandas, and Python CLI, following clean architecture and
    industry-grade design principles.

    This project supports:

        - Web application (Flask + Jinja2)
        - Command Line Interface (CLI)
        - Secure authentication
        - Role-based access (Admin / Member)
        - Transaction-safe book issue & return
        - Analytics & reports using Pandas


ğŸš€ Features

    ğŸ” Authentication & Security

        - Secure password hashing using bcrypt
        - Forced password change on first login
        - Session-based authentication (Flask)
        - Role-based access control (Admin / Member)


    ğŸ‘‘ Admin Capabilities

        - View dashboard with statistics
        - Add / delete users
        - Add / delete books
        - Issue books to members
        - Return books and calculate fines
        - View all users and books
        - Generate analytics and reports


    ğŸ‘¤ Member Capabilities

        - View issued books
        - Track return status and fines
        - View available books


    ğŸ“Š Analytics & Reports (Pandas)

        - Search books by title, author, category
        - Sort books by availability / popularity
        - Filter available & overdue books

        Reports:
            - Most issued books
            - Most active users
            - Monthly issue counts

        - Export reports to CSV and Excel


    ğŸ–¥ï¸ CLI Application

        - Secure CLI login
        - Same business logic as Flask app
        - Admin and Member menus
        - Pandas-powered analytics in terminal
        - IDE & Windows-safe password input


