ğŸ—„ï¸ Database Design

    Tables:

        - users   â†’ user accounts and roles
        - books   â†’ library inventory
        - issues  â†’ issue/return history (transactional)


    Key Design Decisions:

        - Issue records are never deleted
        - Returning a book updates return_date

        This allows:
            - Full audit trail
            - Analytics
            - Reports

        Active issues are identified using:

            WHERE return_date IS NULL


âš™ï¸ Setup Instructions

    1ï¸âƒ£ Create Virtual Environment

        python -m venv .venv
        source .venv/bin/activate        # Linux / Mac
        .venv\Scripts\activate           # Windows


    2ï¸âƒ£ Install Dependencies

        pip install -r requirements.txt


    3ï¸âƒ£ Configure Environment

        Create .env file:

            DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
            DB_PORT=3306
            DB_NAME=library_db
            DB_USER=app_user
            DB_PASSWORD=App@123
            FLASK_SECRET_KEY=super-secret-library-key


    4ï¸âƒ£ Setup Database

        Run the SQL schema:

            source database/schema.sql;


    5ï¸âƒ£ Seed Initial Data

        python database/seed_data.py


â–¶ï¸ Running the Applications

    ğŸŒ Run Flask Web App

